xsd:annotation.xsd:documentation: Defines the report name as it appears in SYSPRO. This report must already exist. Only the "Report" type of report is supported by this Business Object.
Defines the currency to be used for the report.
Indicates whether only report totals should be output. (Y- Yes and N - No. If no value is supplied a default value of 'N' will be used.)
Indicates whether detail lines with zero amounts should be excluded.(Y - Yes and N - No. If no value is supplied a default value of 'Y' will be used.)

If "Y" the business object will only return the prompts required for the specified report. If “Y” the report will not be run, “N” must be specified for the report to be run. (Y - Yes and N - No. If no value is supplied a default value of 'N' will be used.)

Defines the financial period required for reporting. Valid options are: C = Current, P = Previous, Y = Year end, L = Closing and N = Period number. If N is specified the GlPer element below is mandatory.
This element is only required if the ‘Per’ element above is specified with an ‘N’. Possible values are 1 through to 13, depending on the accounting periods per year set for the company.
Indicates the ledger year required. A value of ‘C’ will return the current year and a number between 1 and 9 will return the corresponding previous reporting year.
Defines any numeric value that could be required by the report to be used in calculations. Can be a negative value and can have decimals.
Defines the ledger quarter with a value of ‘C’ for Current quarter, ‘P’ for Previous quarter or 1, 2, 3 or 4 representing a specific quarter.
Defines the date entered at run time. Use the format "YYYY/MM/DD"
Defines any alphanumeric value that could be required by the report.
Defines the pattern for the run time mask. Must have at least one wildcard character.
Defines whether all companies, a range of companies or a single company should be returned. (A - all, R – range, S – single). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'A' will be used.

Up to 15 subtitles can be output. Each subtitle has three elements: ‘ColumnFrom’, ‘ColumnTo’ and ‘ColumnTitle’. ‘ColumnFrom’ and ‘ColumnTo’ are just indications of where the ‘ColumnTitle’ is plotted. It is up to the user to decide how to use this information to print the ’ColumnTitle’.
Up to 15 column headings can be output. ‘ColumnN’ (where N is 1 to 50) is the heading line 1 description and ‘ColumnXn’ (where n is 1 to 50) is a heading line 2 description.

ColumnType indicates the nature of the contents of the detail line. Valid values are ‘A’,’T’ and ‘R’. 'A' means the contents are regular account details. 'T' means this is a total line, which may have under and over lines. 'R' means the detail line is a text line .

‘SkipOption’ indicates how many lines are to be skipped or if a page feed is to be performed before a detail line is printed. Valid values are 0-9 or P. 0 means no lines will be skipped, 1-9 indicates the number of lines to be skipped, P means a page feed will be performed.
Underline character. It is applicable to "T" ColumnTypes only.Valid characters are only '=' for a double line or '-' for a single line.
Overline character. It is applicable to "T" ColumnTypes only.Valid characters are only '=' for a double line or '-' for a single line.
If the element ‘ColumnType’ is a 'T' this element will be populated with the total line description if defined.
